	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'd wait a few levels.  The placeholder for the named Wurms is an undead ape named Gullerback.  He ranges from mid to high 40s and has an extremely high magic resistance (druids, save your mana - I've been in on ten or so Gullerback kills and never seen Snare land on him).  He hits pretty hard but not out of line with his level, 160 isn't an uncommon hit from this guy at all.  He does, however, have a great number of hit points for his level.  A good tough fight for a full group of mid-40s, and I think out of reach for all but the largest or best-equipped groups of 35-40th level characters.<br><br>The good news is, if your group can take Gullerback then you won't have any trouble at all with the named Wurms.<br><br>Grygus<br>Shaman of Halas<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
