	   <tr><td colspan=2>Stats aside, lets assume that a ragebringer and a wyrmslayer are compared, and that whoever has the wyrmslayer also has a 40% haste from somewhere. <br><br>Ragebringer : 15 / 15<br>Wyrmslayer  : 25 / 24<br><br>Now lets assume that they are up to 65% haste<br><br>Ragebringer : 15 / 8.75 = 1.714<br>Wyrmslayer  : 25 / 14   = 1.785<br><br>Wyrmslayer wins on straight ratio here.  Though the str bonus isnt figured in, and the rogue attacking with less delay would get more str bonus damage. <br><br>Oh and for S and G's, ever consider a weighted axe with 65% haste?  Weighted axe?  Whats that?  Its a silly 75/ 150 axe some giants have.  With haste, its 75/52.5= 1.428.  Not a shabby weapon.  Not one I'd ever use though, too damn slow<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
